24 Sec. 10. 5 MRSA §17001, sub-§13, ¶B, as amended by PL 2017, c. 392, §1, is
25 further amended to read:
26 B. For members other than members of the Participating Local District Retirement
27 Program under chapters 425 and 427, "earnable compensation" does not include:
28 (1) For any member who has 10 years of creditable service by July 1, 1993 or who
29 has reached 60 years of age and has been in service for a minimum of one year
30 immediately before that date, payment for more than 30 days of unused
31 accumulated or accrued sick leave, payment for more than 30 days of unused
32 vacation leave or payment for more than 30 days of a combination of both and,
33 effective October 1, 1999, whether or not the member is in service on October 1,
34 1999, the 30-day limitation may not be decreased and the exclusion set out in
35 subparagraph (2) may not be made applicable to such a member; or
36 (2) For any member who is not covered by subparagraph (1), payment for any
37 unused accumulated or accrued sick leave or payment for any unused vacation
38 leave; or.
39 (3) Any other payment that is not compensation for actual services rendered or
40 that is not paid at the time the actual services are rendered.
41 A payment for unused sick leave or unused vacation leave may not be included as part
42 of earnable compensation unless it is paid upon the member's last termination before
43 the member applies for retirement benefits.
